  "Question": "<p><em><strong>Some Background and Motivation:</strong></em> In <a href=\"https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/3161381/why-does-the-integral-domain-being-trapped-between-a-finite-field-extension-im\">this question</a>, it is shown that an integral domain <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_2\"><math alttext=\"D\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>D</mi></semantics></math></span> such that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_3\"><math alttext=\"F\\subset D\\subset E\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>\u2282</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>\u2282</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_4\"><math alttext=\"E\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>E</mi></semantics></math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_5\"><math alttext=\"F\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>F</mi></semantics></math></span> fields with <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_6\"><math alttext=\"[E:F]\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> finite, is itself a field.  However, a significantly more general result holds and seems worthy, of independent address; hence,</p> <p>Let</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_7\"><math alttext=\"F\\subset E\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>\u2282</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>be fields with</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_8\"><math alttext=\"[E:F]&lt;\\infty;\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>E</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi><mo>;</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_9\"><math alttext=\"R\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>R</mi></semantics></math></span> is a ring such that</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_10\"><math alttext=\"F\\subset R\\subset E,\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>\u2282</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2282</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_11\"><math alttext=\"R\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>R</mi></semantics></math></span> is in fact a field.</p>",
